result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI Cause Injury (2+) and PAC Cause Injury (2+). The defendant was found guilty of OWI Cause Injury (2+) and the other charge, PAC Cause Injury (2+) was dismissed by the court.

  • Tracy R Steinke was found guilty of OWI Cause Injury (2+), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(2)(a)1.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Case called at 1:35pm[MO]
Defendant Tracy R Steinke in court, in custody with Attorney Karl Huebner.   ADA Monica Hall  appears for the State of Wisconsin.
 Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of "No Contest" entered on Count #1; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Count #2, #3 and #4.

On Count #1, the Court withholds sentence, and places Defendant on Probation for 2 years, with conditions:

--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with recommended treatment
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment, therapy and counseling as deemed appropriate by the Agent
--to maintain absolute sobriety; no possession or consumption of alcohol or controlled substances without a valid prescription. And to take all prescribed medications as prescribed
--to undergo random drug and alcohol screens
--to obtain/maintain full time employment and/or education program as approved by the Agent
--no presence in bars, tavern, or liquor stores
--no operation of a motor vehicle without BOTH valid DL and Agent approval
--to pay costs of $650 plus costs = $1757 plus $250 DNA surcharge plus $56.74 blood testing costs incurred by the Jefferson Police Deptartment = $1888.74

Days credit for time already served:  59  days
The Court also orders outright (not as conditions of probaton):
--Revocation of drivers license for 27 months
--County alcohol and drug assessment ordered
--Victim impact panel attendance
--Ignition Interlock Device required on any vehicle driven by the Defendant for a 27 month period  

--6 demerit points assessed

Felony Firearm/Voting prohibition warnings given
The Court requires Ms. Steinke to report to Probation by NOON tomorrow.

case called at 10:43am. [MK]
Defendant Tracy R Steinke in court with Attorney Karl Huebner.  DA Susan Happ appears for the State of Wisconsin.
This case was scheduled for Waiver of Preliminary Hearing, and then Plea/Sentencing today.
The Court and counsel address the charges in the Complaint, sorting out that the subject charges are a Class H felony;  Statutes 346.63(2)(a1) and 346.65-(3p) are referenced.  
The Court and counsel discuss victim notification issues.  DA Happ indicates that the State notified victim D.L.W., however the submitted restitution-related information is not complete.  DA Happ is looking into whether J.J., whose car was hit in the collision, is a victim under the definition within Statute 950. 

Ms. Steinke waives her right to Preliminary Hearing; the Court accepts this waiver and binds her over for Trial.
Arraignment:
--service of Information admitted, reading waived
--the charges and maximum penalties are recited
--pleas of "not guilty" are entered by the Court on behalf of Ms. Steinke

The Court indicates that it cannot proceed to Plea/Sentencing today as requested by the Defense; the issue of restitution and victim notification need to be addressed.
On request of the Defense, the Court revokes bond. 
recess 11:03am.
